Bluetongue, Spain
-----------------
Information received on (and dated) 26 Jul 2007 from Dr Lucio Ignacio
Carbajo Goni , Subdirector General de Sanidad Animal, Direccion
General de Ganaderia, Ministerio de Agricultura, Pesca y
Alimentacion, Madrid, Spain
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 18 Jul 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 25 Jul 2007
Report date: 26 Jul 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 26 Jul 2007
Reason for notification: new strain of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: bluetongue virus, serotype 1
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
Report pertains to: defined zone within the country
New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Tarifa, Tarifa, Cadiz (Andalusia)
Date of start of outbreak: 18 Jul 2007
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species: sheep
Susceptible: 300
Cases: 4
Deaths: 0
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Species: cattle
Susceptible: 56
Cases: 0
Deaths: 0
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: low morbidity in the affected farm; no mortality to date.
Summary of outbreaks
Outbreak statistics
Species: sheep
Apparent morbidity rate: 1.33 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 0 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 0 percent
Proportion susceptible removed*: 0 percent
Species: cattle
Apparent morbidity rate: 0 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 0 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: --
Proportion susceptible removed*: 0 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction, or slaughter
Epidemiology
Source of infection: vectors
Epidemiological comments: source of the disease unknown (under investigation)
Control measures
Measures already applied
-movement control inside the country
-zoning
-control of arthropods
-vaccination permitted
-no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: none specified
Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Central Veterinary Laboratory, Algete
(National laboratory)
Tests and results
Species: Sheep
Test: prueba RT-PCR en tiempo real [real-time RT-PCR (reverse
transcription polymerase chain reaction)]
Test date: 25 Jul 2007
Result: positive
